        "subtitle": "The Japanese Vegetable Knife",
        "intro_content": "<p>The <strong>nakiri knife</strong> is a flat-bladed Japanese <strong>kitchen knife</strong> built specifically for vegetable prep. Its squared-off tip and tall blade make the nakiri a favourite among cooks who want clean, precise cuts through everything from onions to leafy herbs. Unlike the santoku or chef knife, the nakiri uses a straight up-and-down push cut rather than a rocking motion. XinZuo nakiri knives feature 67-layer Damascus steel forged in Yangjiang, delivering the thin, hard edge that vegetable work demands. For home cooks who do serious vegetable prep, a dedicated nakiri knife outperforms any all-purpose blade.</p>",
